aris fioretos arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe visiting artists aris fioretos at stanford march 8 2012 hosted at stanford by fsi stanford the europe center workshop fioretos is the special guest for a workshop inspired by the publication of the american edition of his documented biography of the nobel prize winning poet nelly sachs nelly sachs flight and metamorphosis stanford university press 2012 about aris fioretos a professor of aesthetics at sodertorn university in stockholm sweden aris fioretos was educated at stockholm and yale universities the recipient of numerous prizes and fellowships most recently from the swedish academy and all souls college oxford he has published several novels and book length essays and has rendered the works of paul auster friedrich holderlin and vladimir nabokov into swedish his latest award winning novel is entitled the last greek 2009 fioretos is also the general editor of the first commented edition of the complete works of nelly sachs in german more information home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
